text: The Metrobank Center is a 66-floor building in Bonifacio Global City, Taguig, Philippines. In 2017, it replaced the PBCom Tower as the tallest completed building in Metro Manila and in the Philippines. It is a mixed-use building. ==Related pages== * List of tallest buildings in the world * List of tallest structures in the world ==References== Category:2017 establishments in Asia Category:Buildings and structures completed in the 21st century Category:Buildings and structures in the Philippines Category:Skyscrapers in Asia
